dismissalText.commentary: Sulieman Benn c Samaraweera b Mendis 6 (10b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 60

commentTextItems.html: and it's all over! Benn came down the track and looked to loft it away. He got a top edge that flies to Samaraweera at short third-man

commentPostTextItems.html: Sri Lanka win the 3-match series 2-0 and would go into the World Cup as one of the favorites. West Indies, on the other hand never looked to be in the match once Darren Bravo got out. The positive for them is that the middle order is starting to look solid and they can go a long way in the World Cup if Gayle fires
Man of the match is Kumar Sangakkara and Man of the series is Upul Tharanga
Thanks for joining us through the coverage of this series

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Baugh b DJ Bravo 30 (28b 2x4 1x6 34m) SR: 107.14

dismissalComment.html: and that's the wicket! Dilshan pays the price for aggression. He tries to cut a ball close to his body and gets a faint edge back to the keeper. Baugh makes no mistakes and takes the catch. Sanga will walk in now

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga b Benn 39 (52b 5x4 0x6 75m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: now this is against the run of play! Tharanga looks to defend the ball and gets an inside edge that trickles back onto the stumps and dislodges the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Miller b Rampaul 44 (51b 2x4 0x6 59m) SR: 86.27

dismissalComment.html: and there is the mandatory wicket in the Powerplay! Jayawardene looks to pull it away and gets a top edge that flies high and is taken by Miller at short fine-leg

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara b Benn 75 (105b 4x4 1x6 112m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: and Benn has his man as Sanga plays all over it and is yorked. The leg bail falls and now Sri Lanka are in a spot of bother
